
 - If Traffic Class & Flow Control are passed inline, they form a 28
bit field.  this means that following fields (next header, HC2 fields)
are not byte aligned.  However, the implementation will add 4 padding
bits following HC1 fields before the HC2 fields (if present).


 - must match link-layer sender with fragment tag when reconstructing.
 - must add fragment pool to allow out-of-order delivery.
